-stand up please?
-Okay.

cue-11
00:00:39.800 --> 00:00:43.140
-Right. Look, back to back here.
-Okay.

cue-12
00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:48.020
-Now, look, I'm taller than you.
-[laughs] But I'm thinner than you.

cue-13
00:00:48.020 --> 00:00:52.520
Mm, good point. The sentences, "I'm taller
than you," and, "I'm thinner than you,"

cue-14
00:00:52.520 --> 00:00:57.300
-both use the comparative form.
-We use comparatives to compare two people

cue-15
00:00:57.300 --> 00:01:01.780
-or things that are different in some way.
-Listen again to the examples we've just

cue-16
00:01:01.780 --> 00:01:08.780
-used. Where does the word than come?
-I'm taller than you. I'm thinner

cue-17
00:01:08.780 --> 00:01:12.760
-than you.
-Than comes after the comparative

cue-18
00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:17.100
adjective. We usually use than in
comparative sentences.

cue-19
00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:23.660
But not always. For example, I can ask,
"Who is taller? You or me?"

cue-20
00:01:23.660 --> 00:01:28.860
Now, there are different ways to make the
comparative form. For short words, just

cue-21
00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:34.680
add er, that's spelt E-R. So tall becomes
taller.

cue-22
00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:37.220
Thin becomes thinner.

cue-23
00:01:37.940 --> 00:01:44.380
Adjectives like happy, funny, easy, that
end in the sound E spelt with a

cue-24
00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:49.500
Y, add -ier, spelt I-E-R.

cue-25
00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:56.480
-So happy becomes happier.
-Easy becomes easier. An example please,

cue-26
00:01:56.480 --> 00:02:00.920
-Neil.
-English is easier than Chinese.

cue-27
00:02:00.920 --> 00:02:06.160
[laughs] Not if you're Chinese though.
Now, adjectives that have two or more

cue-28
00:02:06.160 --> 00:02:13.100
syllables but don't end in E spelt Y use
more. Neil has some examples.

cue-29
00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:19.360
A tablet is more useful than a laptop. The
film of The Hobbit is more

cue-30
00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:25.440
-exciting than the book.
-Useful has two syllables and exciting has

cue-31
00:02:25.440 --> 00:02:30.760
three, so we say more useful and more
exciting.

