cue-33
00:02:34.740 --> 00:02:39.260
And we're talking about comparatives and
superlatives. We've seen how to use and

cue-34
00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:42.320
-make comparatives.
-Now we're going to tell you what

cue-35
00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:47.560
superlatives are and how to use them.
Sophie, are you good at geography?

cue-36
00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:51.000
-Oh, I'll have a go.
-Okay, here's a question for you. What's

cue-37
00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:56.720
-the longest river in the world?
-Well, the Nile is a very long river, but I

cue-38
00:02:56.720 --> 00:03:00.660
think the longest river in the world is
the Amazon?

cue-39
00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:06.500
And you're right, it is the Amazon. The
longest river is a superlative. We use

cue-40
00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:11.780
superlative forms to compare one person or
thing with several others in a group. We

cue-41
00:03:11.780 --> 00:03:16.060
often use them to say which thing or
person is the greatest, the biggest...

cue-42
00:03:16.060 --> 00:03:21.420
-The most beautiful, the best in some way.
-To make the superlative of short words,

cue-43
00:03:21.420 --> 00:03:26.800
like high, deep, tall, add -est. That's
spelt E-S-T.

cue-44
00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:32.440
So the highest mountain, the deepest
ocean, the tallest person.

cue-45
00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:38.180
And remember to put the before the
adjective. So it's, "I'm the tallest

cue-46
00:03:38.180 --> 00:03:42.480
-person in my family."
-Now, for longer adjectives with two or

cue-47
00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:48.840
more syllables, we use most. Rob, who is
the most famous actor in the world?

cue-48
00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:52.600
Oh, well, there are many, aren't there?
But I think, uh, Brad Pitt is the most

cue-49
00:03:52.600 --> 00:03:58.020
-famous actor in the world.
-The most famous actor, so it's the plus

cue-50
00:03:58.020 --> 00:04:04.340
-most plus adjective.
-For adjectives that end in -y, spelt Y,

cue-51
00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:10.240
like funny and happy, we add -iest. That's
I-E-S-T. Here's an

cue-52
00:04:10.240 --> 00:04:16.300
-example.
-The funniest show on TV is The Simpsons.

cue-53
00:04:16.300 --> 00:04:21.680
Now finally, look out for the irregular
comparatives and superlatives.

cue-54
00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:26.800
My iPhone 5 was better than my iPhone 4,
but the iPhone

cue-55
00:04:27.520 --> 00:04:30.840
6 is the best phone on the market now in
my opinion.

cue-56
00:04:31.780 --> 00:04:37.460
The comparative form of good is better,
and the superlative form is best.

cue-57
00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:42.720
-The comparative of bad is worse.
-And the superlative is worst. Listen to

cue-58
00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:44.160
these examples.

cue-59
00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:52.000
Winters have been bad the last few years.
2012 was worse than 2011, but

cue-60
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:57.000
2013 was the worst winter since records
began.

